INSERT INTO `drainage_works_and_water_works_collections` VALUES (1,'blufpdmwqmp7p740k3zzpf3y','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department','24 June 2015 - 21 June 2019','<p>The LT/HYW BCP is the seventh land-based BCP between Hong Kong and Shenzhen. At present, there are two land-based BCPs at Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok. Owing to geographical constraints, however, these two BCPs have little room for further expansion. Situated between Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok, the LT/HYW BCP will make up for the inadequacies and make cross-boundary transportation and connections between Hong Kong and the eastern part of Guangdong Province as well as the Fujian and Jiangxi Provinces more convenient and efficient. This can help expand Hong Kong&#x27;s economic hinterland.</p><p>It comprises the construction of an approximately 4.6km long dual two-lane Connecting Road connecting the BCP with the proposed Sha Tau Kok Interchange and the associated tunnel ventilation buildings. Provision of sewage collection, treatment and disposal facilities for the BCP and the resite of Chuk Yuen Village and the associated environmental mitigation measures, and Environmental Monitoring and Audit (EM&amp;A)</p>','2025-06-02 07:53:52.550000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.591000',NULL,8,36,'en',1.00),(3,'zddshtdytbm2lw048oe1imcg','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Civil Engineering and Development Department','31 January 2013 - 28 November 2018','<p>The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>This is one of the contract in Wan Chai Development Phase II. It is a large scale Reclamation Project with more than 5 Ha. in size. The Project&#x27;s location is from the Central Reclamation Phase III (CRIII) eastern seawall to the west of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre Extension. The scope of work includes dredging works, seawall works, watermains laying, demolition of existing Expo Drive West Bridge, box culvert extension and stormwater drainage works.</p>','2025-06-02 07:57:34.832000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.619000',NULL,15,36,'en',2.00),(5,'iplvtl785xw4gbtp3yhsygub','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL). The scope of work is included Tunnels Works, Foundation Works, Site Formation Works, Bridge Works, Noise Enclosure Works and Demolition Works. This is a challenging project in terms of geographical location and work complexity, as this construction site will passes through the aged urban town Hung Hom where a huge amount of utilities are underground. Due to the location, extensive TTM arrangements and utilities diversion and/or protection has to be undertaken.</p>','2025-06-02 07:59:55.496000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.144000',NULL,15,36,'en',3.00),(7,'fm84r0s33t681vmf0pmd2yrc','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station\n\n','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The 17-kilometre SCL was a territory-wide strategic railway project involving 10 stations, amongst which Diamond Hill was one of the six interchange stations. Upon the completion of Diamond Hill Station, it will become a new interchange station for the future SCL and the existing Kwun Tong Line.</p><p>The scope of SCL1106 included construction of a new SCL concourse and platforms and a wide array of enhanced facilities including the installation of 3 new lifts, 12 escalators, additional ticket issuing machines, automatic teller machines, shops, and new public toilet facilities. The scope also include the relocation of heritage structures and archaeological diggings.</p>','2025-06-02 08:01:43.418000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.724000',NULL,15,36,'en',4.00),(9,'skpheemenpqd2au3e5rlc2sv','Contract No. DC/2011/04 Reconstruction, Improvement and Rehabilitation of Kai Tak River from Wong Tai Sin Police Station to Tung Tau II Estate','Contract No. DC/2011/04 Reconstruction, Improvement and Rehabilitation of Kai Tak River from Wong Tai Sin Police Station to Tung Tau II Estate','Drainage Services Department','31 October 2011 - 31 December 2019','<p>The scope of work includes reconstruction and rehabilitation of a section of Kai Tak River from Po Kong Village Road to Tung Kwong Road of about 600 metres long; construction of a box culvert of about 400 metres long alongside the Kai Tak River from Wong Tai Sin Police Station to Tung Tai Lane; relocation of affected existing watermains and sewers the associated works including landscaping works and in-situ re-provisioning of an existing footbridge near Tung Tai Lane.</p>','2025-06-02 08:03:18.859000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.011000',NULL,15,36,'en',5.00),(11,'pe64t1by4xv7qck4xlau8qtk','Contract No. DC/2009/24 Harbour Area Treatment Scheme Stage 2A – Upgrading of Preliminary Treatment Works at Sandy Bay, Cyberport, Wah Fu, Aberdeen and Ap Lei Chau','Contract No. DC/2009/24 Harbour Area Treatment Scheme Stage 2A – Upgrading of Preliminary Treatment Works at Sandy Bay, Cyberport, Wah Fu, Aberdeen and Ap Lei Chau','Drainage Services Department','31 August 2011 - 08 January 2018','<p>To improve the water quality of the Victoria Harbour, the Harbour Area Treatment Scheme (HATS) was committed in the late 1980s to be implemented in stages to provide treatment for the sewage collected from the urban areas on both sides of the Harbour. Since its commissioning in late 2001, the HATS Stage 1 system has brought substantial and widespread improvements to the general water quality of the Harbour. Stage 2 was implemented in two phases, Stage 2A and Stage 2B.</p><p>As one of the significant part of the HATS Stage 2A, the works of contract DC/2009/24 include the construction of screens, grit traps, deodourization rooms, workshop and administration buildings, and modification of existing inlet pumping stations at the preliminary treatment works at Sandy Bay, Cyberport, Wah Fu, Aberdeen and Ap Lei Chau.</p>','2025-06-02 08:05:29.937000','2025-07-07 07:05:16.851000',NULL,15,36,'en',6.00),(13,'ghoc9wv9ccbvmjmd98msqp0h','Harbour Area Treatment Scheme Stage 2A – Upgrading of Preliminary Treatment Works at North Point, Wan Chai East and Central (Contract No. DC/2009/23)','Harbour Area Treatment Scheme Stage 2A – Upgrading of Preliminary Treatment Works at North Point, Wan Chai East and Central','Drainage Services Department','01 June 2011 - 22 July 2016','<p>Harbour Area Treatment Scheme  is being implemented in stages to combat water pollution caused by urban development around Victoria Harbour.</p><p>This is one of the Harbour Area Treatment Scheme projects, and its major works includes the construction of fine screen and grit trap buildings, deodorization rooms, administration building and modification of existing inlet pumping stations at the preliminary treatment works at North Point, Wan Chai East and Central.</p>','2025-06-02 08:07:24.084000','2025-07-07 07:05:18.135000',NULL,15,36,'en',7.00),(15,'cbofth62f762wky8jx3yk58k','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Civil Engineering and Development Department','15 July 2009 - 23 August 2013','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the construction of approximately 2.6m long roads within the Project Site including the control, management, maintenance and diversion of existing roads, 2 footbridge FB1 and FB4, associated drainage including box culverts, sewerage and watermain works, enhancement and extension works of existing subways SW1, enhancement works of existing subways SW3 and SW5, landscape hardworks and softworks and environmental mitigation measures.</p><p>The works include realignment of Concorde Road, and construction of local Roads L2, L3, L4 (part) and L15. In conjunction with these roadworks are the associated street furniture, road markings and tra¬c signs, works for the highways structures (Footbridges, Subway, Enhancement Works) across Prince Edward Road East, construction of drainage, sewerage and fresh and salt water supplies systems to serve the Public Rental Housing (PRH) sites and the KTGO.</p><p>The works also include construction of two box culverts BC1 &amp; BC2, a 2.5m x 2.5m box culvert at Road L3 and its connection to the existing Nullah No. 2 and 3.0m x 2.8m box culvert along the amenity strip of Road L2 and its connection to the existing Kai Tak Nullah respectively, demolition of an existing ramp at the EMSD Headquarters ramp at the EMSD Headquarters crossing the Cargo Circuit, abandon the existing Nullah No. 1 and pipes, construction of 5 footpath connections from Road L2 to Subway SW5 and Wang Kong Road, improvement works at Kai Shing Street / Kai Wah Street junction, construction and installation of electrical and mechanical works for the infrastructure serving the early development at the North Apron area including the PRH sites and KTGO, landscape softworks and landscape hardworks.</p>','2025-06-02 08:09:56.473000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.333000',NULL,15,36,'en',8.00),(17,'zf5y4tb5bxenthzrqo9pjn63','Site Formation and Foundation Contract for Community College of City University Building','Site Formation and Foundation Contract for Community College of City University Building\n\n','City University of Hong Kong','06 November 2007 - 20 July 2009','<p>The contract includes temporary site formation and foundation works of the proposed Community College of City University Building</p>','2025-06-02 08:11:30.312000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.642000',NULL,15,36,'en',9.00),(19,'u45g5x2l11k0aref5eyiep79','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun (Contract No.TM/2006/02)','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun\n\n','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 April 2007 - 29 May 2009','<p>The major works in this project consisted of the construction of an approx. 400m long and 10.3m wide two-lane carriageway with a 3.5m wide footpath on both sides section of about 160m long elevated structure over Wong Chu Road was constructed with a total of about 135m of retaining wall structure at both ends of the elevated structure.</p>','2025-06-02 08:12:59.664000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.029000',NULL,15,36,'en',10.00),(21,'gl8o9g42ps4oj7j7ee2glil3','The Construction of an 18-Classroom Primary School at Tai Pak Tin Street, Kwai Chung (Contract No. SS R323)','The Construction of an 18-Classroom Primary School at Tai Pak Tin Street, Kwai Chung\n\n','Architectural Services Department','30 April 2007 - 31 July 2009','<p>The Contract consists of the construction of a primary school with 18 classrooms comprising a 10-storey school block including an assembly hall (overall height 39.50 metres) with pile foundations, associated facilities, drainage and external works. The construction floor area of school building is approx. 8,550 m2.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-02 08:14:44.275000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.967000',NULL,15,36,'en',11.00),(23,'l903j2oryhq07xjw2jr04f76','Vet Hospital (Ocean Park Master Redevelopment Project Contract CS01)','Vet Hospital\n\n','Ocean Park Corporation','26 March 2007 - 31 October 2008','<p>The mojar element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the structure of the Veterinary Hospital including the Pool Block, Office Block &amp; Transformer Room</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of architectural, E&amp;M, BS, Fire Services, Lift, MVAC &amp; the likes within the building of the Veterinary Hospital</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of utility services to the new Veterinary Hospital including Fresh water, salt water, fire services water, control cables</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of drainage &amp; sewerage system for discharging storm water &amp; foul water to the existing system in the vicinity</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation, testing &amp; commissioning of a Life Support System at the Veterinary Hospital</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Transportation of facilities &amp; equipments from the existing Veterinary Hospital to the new Veterinary Hospital upon occupation</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:17:19.019000','2025-07-07 07:05:25.645000',NULL,15,36,'en',12.00),(25,'vbojah5vp35c59jeoifodc1z','Site Formation Contract for Multi-Media Building for City University of Hong Kong','Site Formation Contract for Multi-Media Building for City University of Hong Kong\n\n','City University of Hong Kong','27 December 2006 - 07 January 2008','<p>The major element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Carrying out bulk excavation to lower the Site&#x27;s surface level</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Carrying out soil and rock slope stabilization work</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Carrying out the use of cement soil to fill the slope</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of leakage collection system</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Modification of existing surface water drainage system</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of surface drainage system and diversion of the existing stream cours</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:19:19.001000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.218000',NULL,15,36,'en',13.00),(27,'cfi6kzl75e052uprgovizqjj','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38 (Contract No. EP/SP/52/06)','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38\n\n','Environmental Protection Department','03 July 2006 - 01 January 2010','<p>The EcoPark is a key element of the strategy that aims to promote the local recycling industry and jump-start a sustainable economy by providing long-term land facility for the environmental and recycling industry. By encouraging and promoting the reuse, recovery and recycling of our waste resources and return them to the consumption loop, the EcoPark will help capitalize the potential of the local recycling industry and alleviate the heavy demand of the Hong Kong landfills.</p><p>EcoPark occupies 20 hectares of land in Tuen Mun Area 38 and will be developed in two phases. Phase I of EcoPark (about 8 ha) will be available for occupation towards the end of 2006 and Phase II (about 12 ha) in 2009. Various environmentally friendly features are being used for the first time in Hong Kong, such as the Sun Pipe, Solar power water faucet, and a Green roof just to name a few.</p>','2025-06-02 08:20:40.023000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.044000',NULL,15,36,'en',14.00),(29,'uyfcy3o0xmzpb3bj6yl2k2lh','North Coal Jetty Drainage Improvement Works for Lamma Power Station (Contract No. 05/8007)','North Coal Jetty Drainage Improvement Works for Lamma Power Station\n\n','The Hong Kong Electric Co., Ltd.','10 March 2006 - 31 October 2006','<p>The major highlight of the project is the construction of the drainage system along the decking of the Coal Jetty. The drainage system included the supply and installation of 150DN / 250DN D.I. drainage pipeline and 200DN D.I. discharge pipeline for the collection of the water from the decking of the jetty contaminated during unloading of the coal. The collected effluent is then pumped via the submersible pumps with automatic control system through the discharge pipelines and discharged to the existing Effluent Treatment Plant. The designed discharge rate is about 40cu.m / hour for each sump pit.</p><br/><p>In order to install the pipelines that were designed to be hung underneath the fatty decking, with nothing but the sea underneath, a system of temporary working platform was constructed. The temporary working platform was designed to be supported by the permanent pipeline support brackets installed prior to the erection of the platform. Sections of the working platform were fabricated with steel tubular tubes on shore and transported by sampan, the only suitable means of transport underneath the Coal Jetty, to the place under the jetty where it was erected by chain blocks and fixed to the permanent pipeline support brackets. With the temporary working platform in place, the pipelines were able to be installed easily. Upon completion of the installation the temporary platform was removed by dismantling it into pieces of steel tubular tubes and then transported back to the shore, again, by sampan.</p>','2025-06-02 08:23:12.891000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.271000',NULL,15,36,'en',15.00),(31,'jervje9zniizzctmj4ptt9ox','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long (Contract No. DC/2005/02)','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long','Drainage Services Department','29 December 2005 - 30 June 2010','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of Kam Tin Sewage Pumping Station, Shad Po Sewage Pumping Station and Nam Sang Wai Sewage Pumping Station</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of app. 6.6 km long sewers of dial. Ranging from 300 to 1200mm at Kam Tin and Nam Sang Wai of which app. 0.9 km long sewers to be laid by trench less technique</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of app. 5.7 km long twin rising mains of dial. Ranging from 250 to 900mm at Kam Tin and Nam Sang Wai of which app. 0.9 km long twin rising mains to be laid by trench less technique</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of app. 0.9 km long sewers of dial. Ranging from 300 to 900mm at Au Tau of which app. 0.2 km long sewers to be laid by trench less technique</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works associated with Kam Tin Sewage Pumping Station, Shad Po Sewage Pumping Station and Nam Sang Way Sewage Pumping Station</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Preservation and protection of trees within the site, tree felling and transplantation work associated with the construction of sewage pumping stations, and sewer and rising mains laying works; and</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Any other ancillary works associated with items above including manholes, chambers, road works, foot ways, fences, gates and the like.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and installation of electrical and mechanical equipment for Kam Tin Sewage Pumping Station, Shad Po Sewage Pumping Station and Nam Sang Wai Sewage Pumping Station will be executed under separate concurrent E&amp;M contract</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:25:18.410000','2025-07-07 07:05:25.395000',NULL,15,36,'en',16.00),(33,'vqegjzdb5ovadvuv6eoupxjv','Drainage Improvement in East Kowloon - Package A (Contract No. DC/2004/03)','Drainage Improvement in East Kowloon - Package A\n\n','Drainage Services Department','11 May 2005 - 05 January 2009','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of approx. 5.5km of drains with diameter ranging from 225mm to 2,400mm</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of approx. 3km of watermain with diameter ranging from 100mm to 300mm along the proposed drains using the common trench approach</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:26:54.328000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.243000',NULL,15,36,'en',17.00),(35,'gn07j008aidqhykj3c0a847j','Village Flood Protection Works for Tai Kiu and Shui Pin Tsuen (Contract No. DC/2003/08)','Village Flood Protection Works for Tai Kiu and Shui Pin Tsuen\n\n','Drainage Services Department','20 September 2004 - 22 July 2006','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Tai Kiu Floodwater Pumping Station and Power Supply Building and raft foundation and associated floodwater storage pond</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Flow diversion chamber, underground fuel storage chamber, boundary wall at Tai Kiu</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pui Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station with underground floodwater storage tank on raft foundation</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Discharging chamber, flow intercepting chamber, inlet chamaber and fencing wall at Shui Pin Tsuen</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works associated with the two pumping stations</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Tree transplantation and planting works for Tai Kiu and Shui Pin Tsuen</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:28:48.453000','2025-07-07 07:05:26.051000',NULL,15,36,'en',18.00),(37,'jrbjluj89rqmckdhua98y2pi','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A (Contract No. TP37/03)','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A\n\n','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','<p>This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development.  The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads &amp; bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.</p>','2025-06-02 08:30:09.805000','2025-07-07 07:05:25.545000',NULL,15,36,'en',19.00),(39,'n6stw4uklai541alahn92vch','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road (Contract No. HY/2003/27)','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road\n\n','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p>','2025-06-02 08:31:52.998000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.636000',NULL,15,36,'en',20.00),(41,'vvtepyoy4gjce4nubsk4v1j3','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline\n\n','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-02 08:44:09.254000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.954000',NULL,15,36,'en',21.00),(43,'ncswtin61k5q89r2higcpf6f','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II (Contract No. DC/2001/01)','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II\n\n','Sewerage Projects Division','08 March 2002 - 18 October 2005','<p>The major element of works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 primary sedimentation tanks and the associated primary sludge pumping station with a total footprint of 5060m2</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 aeration tanks and the 2 associated aeration tank control rooms with a total footprint of 7690m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 drainage pumping station with a depth of approximately 8m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 12 final sedimentation tanks with a total footprint of 7150m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 RAS pumping station with a footprint of 450m2, 2 grit classifiers, 2 flume channels and 1 aerated grit channel</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the chambers, ducts, pipes, channels, trenches, drawpits , scum pits, drains, road, air main, and painting works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piled foundations including 400 nos. of 1m diameter bored piles and 878 nos. of 219mm diameter mini piles</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and lay D.I. mild steel and precast concrete pipes with diameter ranging from 200mm to 1600mm, where the total length is approximately 1.5km</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:46:14.620000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.153000',NULL,15,36,'en',22.00),(45,'ztb609fz059jme6wssvmsxt5','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai (Contract No. DC/2000/12)','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai\n','Drainage Services Department','20 December 2001 - 12 March 2004','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station on raft foundation including internal and external finishes and their associated floodwater storage ponds</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Boundary wall at Shui Pin Wai including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Retaining walls at Ma Tin Tsuen including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works, cable ducts and drawpits associated with the two pumping stations</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works at Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Cross road drain at Lau Fau Shan Road and rectangular drainage channels near San Hing Tsuen, Ping Shan</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Other ancillary works associated with items above</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of drainage channels near Wing Ning Wai</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the twin 1200mm diameter pipes and the associated outfall and special manhole</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:48:42.370000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.971000',NULL,15,36,'en',23.00),(47,'stln48vk7u6t862ck3qmk5yh','Transfer Facilities from Butterfly Valley Primary Service Reservoir to Secondary Service Reservoirs in the Metropolitan Area, Stage I Laying of Trunk Mains in Sham Shui Po Area (Contract No. 14/WSD/98)','Transfer Facilities from Butterfly Valley Primary Service Reservoir to Secondary Service Reservoirs in the Metropolitan Area, Stage I Laying of Trunk Mains in Sham Shui Po Area','Water Supplies Department','01 December 1999 - 29 February 2004','<p>Transfer Facilities from Butterfly Valley Primary Service Reservoir to Secondary Service Reservoirs in the Metropolitan Area, Stage I Laying of Trunk Mains in Sham Shui Po Area</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply &amp; lay approx. 2800m of welded steel fresh watermain</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Temporary &amp; permanent diversion of utilities</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Design &amp; implementation of temporary traffic management system</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Road drain improvement works</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:50:20.426000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.251000',NULL,15,36,'en',24.00),(49,'k00a8yy70h1f2r23olu1kus7','Nam Cheong Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-402)','Nam Cheong Station\n\n','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-02 08:53:43.586000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.693000',NULL,15,36,'en',25.00),(51,'oad8c91cle685nr1r0n60rif','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station\n\n','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-02 08:55:16.292000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.390000',NULL,15,36,'en',26.00),(53,'shfm2dtb36g3w68chzobi0xw','Civil and Infrastructure Works (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-601)','Civil and Infrastructure Works\n\n','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities. </p>','2025-06-02 08:56:34.269000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.446000',NULL,15,36,'en',27.00),(55,'vm3mobvnc7sh4xqpmstzdz8c','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III (Contract No. CV/98/01)','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III\n\n','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','<p>Works involved:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of about 700m sloping armoured seawall</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Management of a barging point at Sha Tin Area 47B</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Collection of public fill and reclamation of approx. 17 hectares of seabed at Pak Shek Kok and install prefabricated band drains</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of storm water drainage works including channels, a single cell and a 5 cells box culvert, carry out environmental monitoring and landscape work</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:58:11.795000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.521000',NULL,15,36,'en',28.00),(57,'k5hgwwfd0ilzbo2bct1ndls5','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I (Contract No. TP28/95)','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I\n\n','Territory Development Department','18 March 1998 - 05 May 2003','<p>Construction of 1.6km long trunk road together with 7.3km of water main of size up to 600mm diameter and associated works. These works included: a 450m long rectangular box culvert and a sea outfall; 4 nos. 6m high retaining wall; installation of 234m pavement soil nail and import of 300,000m³ filling material. </p>','2025-06-02 08:59:39.789000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.240000',NULL,15,36,'en',29.00),(59,'mv8bw8f8gyugn0yhiuh2zsf8','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages (Contract No. DC/95/03)','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages\n','Drainage Project Division','20 November 1996 - 26 December 2000','<p>The pumping station on raft foundation and its associated storage pond were the major construction works on site. A total of 1,740m long x 3.5m wide, embankment/access road had to be built for flood protection purposes.</p><br/><p>The floodwater flows into the chambers &amp; the pipes system and then to the storage pond. The 5-trough pumping station would begin operating when the floodwater comes up to a certain level upon which the floodwater would pass through a twin-cell box culvert and flow downstream.</p><br/><p>A series of water diversions were required to maintain the stream flow from the San Tin Villages out to the Shen Zhen River.</p><br/><p>For the slope embankment, precast concrete grasscrete blocks are the final surface above the layer of the concrete lining, granular fill &amp; general fill. The grasscrete blocks were designed with open area for hydroseeding and they have to be reinforced together in order to avoid the tidal effect of the floodwater.</p><br/><p>The major difficulties involved in the project were the ground water flow from the adjacent fish ponds and the limited working area along the embankment. Temporary cofferdams formed with sheet piles had to installed in order to cut off the underground water for construction purpose.</p>','2025-06-02 09:01:04.718000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.129000',NULL,15,36,'en',30.00),(61,'zf6qsb8yokssfgt2ne1cu821','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun (TMTL 393)','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun\n\n','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','<p>This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works. </p>','2025-06-02 09:02:46.298000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.672000',NULL,15,36,'en',31.00),(63,'umlpf8uk7rnu6sd20to3jw1u','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works (Contract No. CV/95/14)','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works\n\n','Civil Engineering Department','01 May 1996 - 30 September 1997','<p>The Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Excavation of some 500,000m3 of soil and rock</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Land filling of waste</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works and roadworks</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Site preparatory works</li></ul>','2025-06-02 09:04:14.936000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.095000',NULL,15,36,'en',32.00),(65,'j5vfcl2neudgsrignkq1g5hh','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan (Contract No. SS C410)','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan\n\n','Architectural Services Department','01 January 1995 - 02 January 1998','<p>Construction of two covered spectator stands together with drainage and waterworks, landscaping, M&amp;E works and sports facilities. </p>','2025-06-02 09:05:29.198000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.209000',NULL,15,36,'en',33.00),(67,'dytfuzt03391hx0din7n29u8','土木工程拓展署合約編號CV/2013/08 - 蓮塘/香園圍口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合約六','土木工程拓展署合約編號CV/2013/08 - 蓮塘/香園圍口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合約六\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2015 年 06 月 24 日 - 2019 年 06 月 21 日','<p>蓮塘/香園圍口岸是香港、深圳之間第七個陸路口岸。現時文錦渡和沙頭角兩個陸路口岸，礙於地理限制，難有再擴建的空間。蓮塘/香園圍口岸位於文錦渡和沙頭角之間，正好填補這個不足，使香港與廣東省東部地區以至福建及江西的跨境交通連接更方便快捷。新口岸在策略上對推動長遠經濟發展十分重要。</p><p>興建一條4.6公里的雙程雙線分隔主幹道以連接沙頭角公路交匯處及新口岸，提供排水/排污、水務及新口岸的公共設施工程，另外處理竹園村的遷移，相關的環境緩解措施，以及環境監測及稽核。</p>','2025-06-03 01:08:42.701000','2025-07-07 07:05:12.537000',NULL,15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',1.00),(69,'x670psnkn0n548431v08knyh','合約編號: HK/2012/08 灣仔發展計劃第二期–中環灣仔繞道灣仔西段','合約編號: HK/2012/08 灣仔發展計劃第二期–中環灣仔繞道灣仔西段\n','土木工程拓展署','2013 年 01 月 31 日 - 2018 年 11 月 28 日','<p>灣仔發展計劃第二期為灣仔北和北角提供土地，用以興建中環及灣仔繞道和東區走廊連接路。工程將會為新增的土地發展成世界級海濱長廊供市民享用，同時亦有助紓緩灣仔附近一帶的交通問題</p>