g machines, automatic teller machines, shops, and new public toilet facilities. The scope also include the relocation of heritage structures and archaeological diggings.</p>','2025-06-02 08:01:43.418000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.724000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.005000',15,36,'en',4.00),(425,'ztb609fz059jme6wssvmsxt5','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai (Contract No. DC/2000/12)','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai\n','Drainage Services Department','20 December 2001 - 12 March 2004','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station on raft foundation including internal and external finishes and their associated floodwater storage ponds</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Boundary wall at Shui Pin Wai including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Retaining walls at Ma Tin Tsuen including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works, cable ducts and drawpits associated with the two pumping stations</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works at Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Cross road drain at Lau Fau Shan Road and rectangular drainage channels near San Hing Tsuen, Ping Shan</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Other ancillary works associated with items above</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of drainage channels near Wing Ning Wai</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the twin 1200mm diameter pipes and the associated outfall and special manhole</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:48:42.370000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.971000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.188000',15,36,'en',23.00),(426,'vvtepyoy4gjce4nubsk4v1j3','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline\n\n','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-02 08:44:09.254000','2025-07-07 07:05:27.954000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.202000',15,36,'en',21.00),(427,'umlpf8uk7rnu6sd20to3jw1u','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works (Contract No. CV/95/14)','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works\n\n','Civil Engineering Department','01 May 1996 - 30 September 1997','<p>The Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Excavation of some 500,000m3 of soil and rock</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Land filling of waste</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works and roadworks</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Site preparatory works</li></ul>','2025-06-02 09:04:14.936000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.095000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.264000',15,36,'en',32.00),(428,'ncswtin61k5q89r2higcpf6f','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II (Contract No. DC/2001/01)','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II\n\n','Sewerage Projects Division','08 March 2002 - 18 October 2005','<p>The major element of works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 primary sedimentation tanks and the associated primary sludge pumping station with a total footprint of 5060m2</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 aeration tanks and the 2 associated aeration tank control rooms with a total footprint of 7690m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 drainage pumping station with a depth of approximately 8m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 12 final sedimentation tanks with a total footprint of 7150m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 RAS pumping station with a footprint of 450m2, 2 grit classifiers, 2 flume channels and 1 aerated grit channel</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the chambers, ducts, pipes, channels, trenches, drawpits , scum pits, drains, road, air main, and painting works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piled foundations including 400 nos. of 1m diameter bored piles and 878 nos. of 219mm diameter mini piles</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and lay D.I. mild steel and precast concrete pipes with diameter ranging from 200mm to 1600mm, where the total length is approximately 1.5km</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:46:14.620000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.153000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.325000',15,36,'en',22.00),(429,'mv8bw8f8gyugn0yhiuh2zsf8','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages (Contract No. DC/95/03)','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages\n','Drainage Project Division','20 November 1996 - 26 December 2000','<p>The pumping station on raft foundation and its associated storage pond were the major construction works on site. A total of 1,740m long x 3.5m wide, embankment/access road had to be built for flood protection purposes.</p><br/><p>The floodwater flows into the chambers &amp; the pipes system and then to the storage pond. The 5-trough pumping station would begin operating when the floodwater comes up to a certain level upon which the floodwater would pass through a twin-cell box culvert and flow downstream.</p><br/><p>A series of water diversions were required to maintain the stream flow from the San Tin Villages out to the Shen Zhen River.</p><br/><p>For the slope embankment, precast concrete grasscrete blocks are the final surface above the layer of the concrete lining, granular fill &amp; general fill. The grasscrete blocks were designed with open area for hydroseeding and they have to be reinforced together in order to avoid the tidal effect of the floodwater.</p><br/><p>The major difficulties involved in the project were the ground water flow from the adjacent fish ponds and the limited working area along the embankment. Temporary cofferdams formed with sheet piles had to installed in order to cut off the underground water for construction purpose.</p>','2025-06-02 09:01:04.718000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.129000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.362000',15,36,'en',30.00),(430,'j5vfcl2neudgsrignkq1g5hh','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan (Contract No. SS C410)','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan\n\n','Architectural Services Department','01 January 1995 - 02 January 1998','<p>Construction of two covered spectator stands together with drainage and waterworks, landscaping, M&amp;E works and sports facilities. </p>','2025-06-02 09:05:29.198000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.209000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.441000',15,36,'en',33.00),(431,'stln48vk7u6t862ck3qmk5yh','Transfer Facilities from Butterfly Valley Primary Service Reservoir to Secondary Service Reservoirs in the Metropolitan Area, Stage I Laying of Trunk Mains in Sham Shui Po Area (Contract No. 14/WSD/98)','Transfer Facilities from Butterfly Valley Primary Service Reservoir to Secondary Service Reservoirs in the Metropolitan Area, Stage I Laying of Trunk Mains in Sham Shui Po Area','Water Supplies Department','01 December 1999 - 29 February 2004','<p>Transfer Facilities from Butterfly Valley Primary Service Reservoir to Secondary Service Reservoirs in the Metropolitan Area, Stage I Laying of Trunk Mains in Sham Shui Po Area</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply &amp; lay approx. 2800m of welded steel fresh watermain</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Temporary &amp; permanent diversion of utilities</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Design &amp; implementation of temporary traffic management system</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Road drain improvement works</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:50:20.426000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.251000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.500000',15,36,'en',24.00),(432,'k5hgwwfd0ilzbo2bct1ndls5','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I (Contract No. TP28/95)','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I\n\n','Territory Development Department','18 March 1998 - 05 May 2003','<p>Construction of 1.6km long trunk road together with 7.3km of water main of size up to 600mm diameter and associated works. These works included: a 450m long rectangular box culvert and a sea outfall; 4 nos. 6m high retaining wall; installation of 234m pavement soil nail and import of 300,000m³ filling material. </p>','2025-06-02 08:59:39.789000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.240000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.548000',15,36,'en',29.00),(433,'oad8c91cle685nr1r0n60rif','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station\n\n','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-02 08:55:16.292000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.390000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.654000',15,36,'en',26.00),(434,'shfm2dtb36g3w68chzobi0xw','Civil and Infrastructure Works (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-601)','Civil and Infrastructure Works\n\n','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities. </p>','2025-06-02 08:56:34.269000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.446000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.711000',15,36,'en',27.00),(435,'n6stw4uklai541alahn92vch','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road (Contract No. HY/2003/27)','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road\n\n','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p>','2025-06-02 08:31:52.998000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.636000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.822000',15,36,'en',20.00),(436,'vm3mobvnc7sh4xqpmstzdz8c','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III (Contract No. CV/98/01)','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III\n\n','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','<p>Works involved:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of about 700m sloping armoured seawall</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Management of a barging point at Sha Tin Area 47B</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Collection of public fill and reclamation of approx. 17 hectares of seabed at Pak Shek Kok and install prefabricated band drains</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of storm water drainage works including channels, a single cell and a 5 cells box culvert, carry out environmental monitoring and landscape work</li></ul>','2025-06-02 08:58:11.795000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.521000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.815000',15,36,'en',28.00),(437,'zf6qsb8yokssfgt2ne1cu821','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun (TMTL 393)','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun\n\n','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','<p>This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works. </p>','2025-06-02 09:02:46.298000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.672000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.846000',15,36,'en',31.00),(438,'k00a8yy70h1f2r23olu1kus7','Nam Cheong Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-402)','Nam Cheong Station\n\n','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-02 08:53:43.586000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.693000','2025-07-07 07:05:28.924000',15,36,'en',25.00);
